This occasion calls for a special record to celebrate our lustrum. We’ve teamed up with the amazing Canadian singer Riell, who helped us write the most personal lyrics our music has ever known.‘Rulers of the night’ is our anthem to celebrate 10 years of Blasterjaxx. One decade passed, many more to follow! Thank you for your endless support.
Love, Thom and Idir

2020 has been a different and difficult year for everyone around the world. To celebrate in style that we can finally leave this year behind us we decided to create a special New Year’s Eve Mix with all the greatest dance hits out there. Play this on the 31st and celebrate the start of 2021 with some great music!

I couldn't be anything less than super grateful to have you guys by my side. That's why I want to give a BIG thank you to all of those who are supporting me in this crazy, but AMAZING journey. 

When I started making music 4 years ago, I could never imagine that I would play around this beautiful globe and meet all of you guys. I could never imagine you guys singing along with my songs. I couldn't even imagine to meet some of MY idols who made me realize I wanted to make music as well.

I got a lot of messages from people who already voted for me, you guys are the best!

Never stop dreaming, I won't either.

Never stop dreaming, I won't either.

Much love – Melle

Spinnin’ Records has proudly announced the fourth edition of its renowned Spinnin’ Hotel during this year’s Miami Music Week. Taking place from Wednesday the 27th to Sunday the 31st of March, the event will feature five consecutive pool parties showcasing some of the label's most well-known artists. VsC9sprk2UE.description:
Spinnin’ Records has proudly announced the fourth edition of its renowned Spinnin’ Hotel during this year’s Miami Music Week. Taking place from Wednesday the 27th to Sunday the 31st of March, the event will feature five consecutive pool parties showcasing some of the label's most well-known artists. Tickets are available now: https://spinnin.lnk.to/SpinninHotel2019

On Friday 21 July, Spinnin’ Sessions hosted its own area at renowned German festival Parookaville, presenting a sweet set of Spinnin’ artists throughout the day. Wanna look back, or see what went down over there? Check out the official aftermovie right now!

jLAbdAc6GVQ.title: Spinnin' Hotel Miami 2017 | Official Aftermovie
jLAbdAc6GVQ.description:
Spinnin’ Records has proudly announced the fourth edition of its renowned Spinnin’ Hotel during this year’s Miami Music Week. Taking place from Wednesday the 27th to Sunday the 31st of March, the event will feature five consecutive pool parties showcasing some of the label's most well-known artists. Tickets are available now: https://spinnin.lnk.to/SpinninHotel2019

Last month, from Wednesday 22 March to Sunday 26 March, we presented the second edition of the renowned Spinnin’ Hotel, a five-day pool party during the Miami Music Week, hosted by Spinnin’ Sessions, DOORN Records, Heartfeldt, Spinnin’ Premium and Spinnin’ Deep. It was quite a ride, as you can see in this official aftermovie! Thanks to everyone who joined us, and to everyone else; we hope you get a sweet taste of our Miami vibe here :)
 
Wanna listen to some of our musical highlights at this year’s Miami Music Week, check out our official After Miami Mix: https://www.youtube.com/watch?v=p4yN74opq6U

Xjbgyu7OZRM.title: KSHMR, B3nte & Badjack - The Spook Returns (Official Music Video)
Xjbgyu7OZRM.description:
Best of KSHMR - KSHMR MIX 2020: https://youtu.be/SKXPmV3L3Jo

KSHMR, B3nte & Badjack - The Spook Returns is OUT NOW on Spinnin' Premium. Like this track? Download on Beatport or add it to your favourite Spotify/Apple Music playlist by clicking HERE: https://spinninpremium.lnk.to/TheSpookReturns!YT

Join our Spinnin' Records Top 100 Playlist ► https://spinninrecords.lnk.to/top100!YT

KSHMR, the number 12 DJ of the world, joins forces with Swedish producer B3nte and Badjack for The Spook Returns. UIJxoINt7qo.title: Far East Movement - Fighter ft. Yoonmirae & Autolaser (Official Music Video)
UIJxoINt7qo.description:
Far East Movement - Identity is OUT NOW! Like this track or want to listen the other tracks on the album? Check it out on Spotify or Apple Music: https://FarEastMovement.lnk.to/Identity!YT

Join our Spinnin' Records Top 100 Playlist ► https://spinninrecords.lnk.to/top100!YT

Hip-hop trio Far East Movement presents their new album Identity. This is a versatile collection that you cannot afford to miss and if you do, you will miss out on some very epic musical highlights. Far East Movement joined with multiple talented artists like Macy Gray, Marshmello, Soulja Boy and more, to give each tune an amazing quality and flavor of its own. One thing all tracks have in common is its raw vibe that you got to love and embrace. Far East Movement welcomes you into their amazing world! 

"This song is reflective of our own lives and careers where there have been so many instances where we wanted to give up. Creating this positive and inspirational tone was in fact therapeutic for us. the whole album theme is a far east movement identity, so for the music video with Yoon Mirae we wanted to pay respect to the early korean and asian immigrants that were either forced here from conflict or came here with a dream and made it possible for something like the far east movement to even exist. Sadly in today's news, when we hear politicians and talk radio hosts stances on letting people into the US we can only think, 'what if they did that to all the Asian groups that had no where to go and ended up here?' the music vid is symbolic of us finding our own way and identity. We have wanted to officially collaborate with the legendary Yoon Mirae for years, she is someone who's credibilty and longevity in the korean music scene is a testament to her skills and fight. We also collaborated with a norwegian artist and one of the most innovative musicians in the game, who we recently signed to our company Transparent Agency with Trapcity named Autolaser. Thank you for taking this journey with us and we hope you enjoy the album." -FM

F_S9T1ax2nU.title: QUINTINO - F WHAT YOU HEARD (Official Music Video)
F_S9T1ax2nU.description:
QUINTINO - GO HARDER EP PART 2 is OUT NOW! Like this track? Add it to your favourite Spotify/Apple Music playlist by clicking HERE: https://quintino.lnk.to/GoHarderEPPart2

Join our Spinnin' Records Top 100 Playlist ► https://spinninrecords.lnk.to/top100!YT

Quintino is going harder than ever! He now drops 5 tracks on his follow up EP called GO HARDER PART 2. It’s not a secret that this Dutch musical hero is exploring several genres. This EP is the proof that he’s skilled to master all genres. 

In F WHAT YOU HEARD, you will notice some nice trap influences intertwined with up-pitched vocal samples followed by a massive drop. 

WORK IT is a huge banger that contains hard kicks, a trilling bass and a big drop enhanced by a powerful synth lead. 

YOU DON'T STOP is fueled by many beats per minute and gets the image of a trap tune cause of its hi-hats and steel drums. 

EMF is the result of joined forces between Quintino and Crossnaders. This electric fire shows distorted kicks, vivacious synths and pitch bended leads. 

And last but not least Quintino teamed up with Killfake for floor filler UNDERCOVERS. With its twerk beat and uplifting chords, this is definitely a great asset to the Go Harder Part 2 EP!

Follow Quintino:

aNwgj4etC_4.title: Sam Feldt feat. Bright Sparks - We Don't Walk We Fly (Official Music Video)
aNwgj4etC_4.description:
Sam Feldt - Been A While EP is OUT NOW! Grab your copy HERE: http://samfeldt.lnk.to/BeenAWhileEP

Stay up to date on more Spinnin' artists & music here! ► http://spinninrecords.com

Impressive tour de force by Sam Feldt, delivering a six-track EP filled with deep house gems. Been A While is already making waves as one of early 2016’s most popular tunes, while Sam’s collab with Dante Klein featuring Milow is also destined to become a vocal house classic. 
His melodic approach, filled with sweet chords progressions and organic sounds also works wonders for the Lulleaux collab All The Kids, bringing nice singalong chorus and string sentiments. 
We Don’t Walk We Fly shows Sam’s energetic side, blasting an uptempo deep house groove while Bright Sparks provides an exciting vocal performance - peaktime music for sure! 

Another tune perfecting the emotionally driven sounds of Sam is Hungry Eyes, with Meleka as a shining star above wonderfully arranged melodies, lifting you up and hitting you right in the heart. Finally, Forgiveness brings wonderful piano chords into Sam’s world, accented with lovely strings and touching vocals of Joe Cleere.

As said, Sam Feldt at his best with this EP, the Dutchman surpassing himself with a unique and overwhelmingly beautiful song collection.

Follow Sam Feldt: 
https://soundcloud.com/samfeldt
http://www.twitter.com/samfeldtmusic
http://www.facebook.com/officialsamfeldt

Camera & Editing: Deni Kukura

Visual effects: Dzanar Abbas-Zade

Stay up to date on more Spinnin' artists & music here! ► http://spinninrecords.com

Impressive tour de force by Sam Feldt, delivering a six-track EP filled with deep house gems. Been A While is already making waves as one of early 2016’s most popular tunes, while Sam’s collab with Dante Klein featuring Milow is also destined to become a vocal house classic. 
His melodic approach, filled with sweet chords progressions and organic sounds also works wonders for the Lulleaux collab All The Kids, bringing nice singalong chorus and string sentiments. 
We Don’t Walk We Fly shows Sam’s energetic side, blasting an uptempo deep house groove while Bright Sparks provides an exciting vocal performance - peaktime music for sure! 

Another tune perfecting the emotionally driven sounds of Sam is Hungry Eyes, with Meleka as a shining star above wonderfully arranged melodies, lifting you up and hitting you right in the heart. Finally, Forgiveness brings wonderful piano chords into Sam’s world, accented with lovely strings and touching vocals of Joe Cleere.

As said, Sam Feldt at his best with this EP, the Dutchman surpassing himself with a unique and overwhelmingly beautiful song collection.

Follow Sam Feldt:

http://www.twitter.com/samfeldtmusic
http://www.facebook.com/officialsamfeldt

av_J7bgUSKI.title: SASH! vs Olly James - Ecuador (Official Music Video)
av_J7bgUSKI.description:
SASH! vs Olly James - Ecuador is OUT NOW! Grab your copy HERE: https://spinnin.lnk.to/Ecuador

Stay up to date on more Spinnin' artists & music here! ► http://spinninrecords.com

One of dance music’s most legendary tunes getting revived here, as Olly James lets the classic Sash! record Ecuador return in a 21st century guise. The melody and vocal input remains as catchy as it always was, the chords have gotten a serious makeover, moving into mainstage electro territory, just as the kicks draw a harder vibe than the original. Making this a worthy return of the track, destined for another round of hit success!

It’s all love here, What is destined for some 2015 highlights.

Video By Bosco Shane (www.boscoshane.com)

iXIDtf1wP0g.description:
Download on iTunes NOW : http://smarturl.it/garrixmoti_virus
Martin Garrix & MOTi present Virus (How About Now). 

Grab your copy on Beatport NOW : http://btprt.dj/1z3ITS1

Subscribe to Spinnin' Records here : http://bit.ly/SPINNINTV

Rumors have been scouring the internet regarding this one particular track all the major DJs have been dropping in their recent sets. People have been trying to figure out who is behind this mystery track for months and now Spinnin’ Records is happy to reveal that Martin Garrix, one of the biggest and youngest big-room, big-stage DJs, is stepping up for a new milestone in his fast-paced career. Garrix is expanding his sizeable music catalogue with smashing VIRUS; a collaboration with buzz-worthy producer and Tiesto’s protégé MOTi, who recently released the electro crowd pleaser Zeus on Musical Freedom together with Kenneth G. VIRUS has us falling in love with Big Room over and over again. Way to start the new club season!

4jd6_uQuO0I.title: New World Sound & Thomas Newson - Flute (Official Music Video)
4jd6_uQuO0I.description:
Check out the official music video for New World Sound & Thomas Newson - Flute. 
Download on iTunes: http://smarturl.it/itunes_flute

Grab your copy on Beatport NOW : http://btprt.dj/17Z1IGY
Subscribe to Spinnin' TV here : http://bit.ly/SPINNINTV

New World Sound joins forces with up and coming Thomas Newson for a massive collaboration on brand new single 'Flute', to go out on DOORN on 11th November. 
 
A 50 second preview was released last week hyping the video as a tantalising teaser for the track, which already racked up over 180,000 views on Youtube and hit #1 in the ADE Buzz Chart. The ID left everybody under the impression it was a new collab from W&W and Blasterjaxx. Originally keeping the artists a secret Spinnin' reveals now the genius behind the track as New World Sound and Thomas Newson. 
 
Built around the haunting pan flute that leads into a thumping bassline, the track combines an intense riff at the core of the track layered with the classical flute to create a peak time dance floor filler.
 
New World Sound aka 21 and 19 year old brothers Tyrone and Jesse Taylor are two DJ/ Producers currently dominating their homeland around the Gold Coast of Australia, and the world. Their first release 'Peak' earned them huge support from artists such as Tiesto, Ferry Corsten and Judge Jules as well as a score of other hugely influential artists.
 
New World Sound emerged from the studio again in October 2012 with 'Bantam', a dubstep infused club banger, and received praise from the Grammy Award winning David Guetta, placing it on his monthly top 10 Beatport chart and playing it twice on his F**k Me I'm Famous podcast. The release of 'Aye' in June 2013 marked the duo's signing to Avicii's label LE7ELS and earned New World Sound their first ever BBC Radio 1 play during Pete Tong's weekly essential collection show. They host a weekly radio show on Australia's premiere Dance Music Station, Radio Metro.
 
Thomas Newson is only 19 year old, yet he looks set to be one of the next up and coming producers. With support from Hardwell dropping his track 'Pallaroid' during his explosive set at Tomorrowland this year, this relative newcomer is one to look out for.
---

s-OshBSx3vg.title: Dimitri Vegas & Like Mike vs Sander van Doorn - Project T (OUT NOW)
s-OshBSx3vg.description:
DIMITRI VEGAS, LIKE MIKE & SANDER VAN DOORN UNVEIL "PROJECT T" Download on Beatport: http://btprt.dj/133UD5r

'Project T', the track that launched the official Tomorrowland 2012 Aftermovie and had over 88 million YouTube viewers salivating at the sound, is finally out exclusively on Beatport!

Both artists need no introduction, but for those with a passion for statistics, 2013 has been a truly incredible year for both. Sander van Doorn is without a doubt one of the world's most essential and popular DJ/Producers in dance music today. Every single SVD track this year has entered the Beatport Top 10, continuing to confirm his status as one of the most influential and celebrated artists in electronic music history.

Similarly, Belgian brothers Dimitri & Mike have experienced their most successful year to date, with three of their tracks hitting the Beatport #1 (Mammoth, Turn It Up & Chattahoochee) plus fan favourite Wakanda scoring the #2 spot, their ever-growing global army of fans getting behind each and every hit to huge effect.

Even more train-spotting facts for fans After the release of Sander's smash hit 'Outro' in 2011, the trio hooked up at several festivals around the world and began formulating a plan to completely reinvent the record together. Containing all the exhilarating builds and monumental drops Dimitri & Mike are world-renowned for, the two brothers combine seamlessly with Sander to create a tender and emotional sound that will leave the ears of music lovers everywhere longing for more. 

#1 Buzz Chart : 'The perfect production for sunsets and sunrises Worldwide, the beauty with the beast!'
David Guetta : 'Dimitri and Mike deliver again with huge support from Sander! Rocking!
Nicky Romero : 'Supported in my rradioshow'
Armin van Buuren : 'Nice'
Steve Aoki : 'Thanks for sending!'
Dada Life : 'okay!'
Bingo Players : 'Nice track'

The official music video for Afrojack's 'Rock The House'! Subscribe to Spinnin' TV now: http://www.youtube.com/SpinninTV

When Afrojack dropped 'Rock The House' at Ultra Music Festival earlier this year, he instantly knew this had to become one of his next singles, and if you'd just listen to it you will understand why! Still sticking to his trademark filthy Dutch electro sounds, Afrojack creates a more melodic buildup to what is one of the most epic drops you've heard in a while. Want to make your audience go crazy like you've never seen before? All you have to do is drop this track, success guaranteed.

FavtnZjzVXg.description:
Download on Beatport: http://bit.ly/TEACUP
Spotify: http://spoti.fi/SpinninRadio

Facebook: http://facebook.com/SpinninRecords
Twitter: http://twitter.com/SpinninRecords

http://youtube.com/spinninTV presents : Rune RK - Teacup (Original Mix)

Rune RK's worldwide monster hit 'Calabria' sold more than 4 million singles, reached the #1 spot on Billboard's Hot Dance Airplay chart and gathered a collective 50 million (!) views on Youtube. Now the Danish producer is back with Teacup. The video for this track went viral within hours after its release and features an awesome amount of fine china being smashed by barely dressed ladies. One thing's for sure, you need to see it for yourself. Teacup is pure dance floor power! 

Tiesto : '3 times in a row in my radioshow!'
Avicii : 'supporting!'
Pete Tong : 'Supported in my BBC Radio 1 show as 'Essential Contender'!'
Arty : 'Played in my radioshow!'
Leon Bolier : 'nice, great melody!'
Gareth Emery : 'nice track!'
A-Trak : 'support!'
Thomas Gold : 'cooool!'
Danny Howard / BBC Radio 1 : 'One of my Tunes Of The Summer! SO Good.'
Jordan Suckley / BBC Radio 1 : 'Great track'
Directed by Jonas Bech & Kristian Ussing
D.O.P: Snorre Ruhe
Gaffer: Michel Copeland Toft
Best boy: Oliver Mariager
Production manager: Henrik Voigt
Edit: Boathouse
